APA還透過援引{{link-en|唐納德·F·羅伯茲|Donald F. Roberts}}等人的研究進一步地探究輕少年雜誌市場，發現「在8至18歲的女孩之中，有47%的人每天會讀前一天的雜誌至少五分鐘」<ref name="APA" /><ref>{{cite report |last1= Roberts |first1= Donald F. |last2= Foehr |first2= Ulla G. |last3= Rideout |first3= Victoria |author-link1= Donald F. Roberts |date= March 2005 |title= Generation M: media in the lives of 8-18 year olds |url= http://kff.org/other/generation-m-media-in-the-lives-of/ |publisher= [[Kaiser_Family_Foundation|Kaiser Family Foundation]] |location= Menlo Park, California |access-date= 2017-01-31 |archive-date= 2020-11-27 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201127015820/https://www.kff.org/other/generation-m-media-in-the-lives-of/ |dead-url= no }} [https://kaiserfamilyfoundation.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/generation-m-media-in-the-lives-of-8-18-year-olds-report.pdf Pdf.] {{Wayback|url=https://kaiserfamilyfoundation.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/generation-m-media-in-the-lives-of-8-18-year-olds-report.pdf |date=20170215021337 }}</ref>。這些雜誌大多聚焦在一個主題，表現自己對男性的性慾望。這在 Duffy 和 Gotcher的研究中被稱為「誘惑的化妝」（costuming for seduction）。<ref name="APA" /><ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Duffy | first1 = Margaret | last2 = Gotcher | first2 = J. Micheal | title = Crucial advice on how to get the guy: the rhetorical vision of power and seduction in the teen magazine ''YM'' | journal = [[Journal_of_Communication_Inquiry|Journal of Communication Inquiry]] | volume = 20 | issue = 1 | page = 38 | publisher = [[SAGE_Publications|Sage]] | date = April 1996 | url = http://jci.sagepub.com/content/by/year | ref = harv | postscript = . | access-date = 2017-01-31 | archive-date = 2016-12-11 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20161211134840/http://jci.sagepub.com/content/by/year | dead-url = no }} [https://www.researchgate.net/publication/281903852_Crucial_Advice_on_How_to_Get_the_Guy ResearchGate pdf] {{Wayback|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/281903852_Crucial_Advice_on_How_to_Get_the_Guy |date=20180719054604 }}.</ref>

==== 認知情形與精神影響 ====
研究發現，將自己的身體與文化塑造的性化形象進行比對、可能會攪亂女孩的精神，女孩的性化和物化會破壞她們對自己身體的自信心和安定感，導致情緒的波動和自我認同出現問題，例如引發焦慮和羞恥感。<ref name=APA />

研究已經找到性化與女性最常被診斷出的三種精神健康問題的關聯性：飲食失調、自卑、憂鬱症或憂鬱症狀<ref name=APA />。還認為女孩的性化對女孩發展健康的性自我形象的能力有負面影響。<ref name=APA />

媒體對女孩性化的後果是，年輕女孩正在「學習如何將自己視為性對象」<ref name=Dewar />，當女孩子無法滿足理想和主流文化的標準時，她們可能會心生焦慮<ref name=Dewar />。性化對於年輕孩童在性身份上的發展是有負面影響的，他們可能會尋求與性相關的媒介，並認為把自己變成性玩物是可以被允許的。<ref name=Kilbourne />

