性化也是媒體研究和文化研究學者的爭論議題。在這個情境中、這個術語並非單純地用來表示一個社會問題，而是用來表示性別的型式在媒體與文化裡出現了更多、更廣泛的涵義<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Attenborough | first1 = Frederick T. | author-link1 = Frederick T. Attenborough | title = Complicating the sexualization thesis: The media, gender and 'sci-candy'|journal = [[Discourse_&_Society|Discourse & Society]] | volume = 22| issue = 6| pages = 659–675 | publisher = [[SAGE_Publications|Sage]] | doi = 10.1177/0957926511411693 | date = November 2011 | url = http://dx.doi.org/10.1177/0957926511411693 | ref = harv| postscript = .}} [https://www.academia.edu/7593771/Complicating_the_sexualisation_thesis_the_media_gender_and_sci-candy Online.]</ref>，包括：
在各式媒體裡、對性的價值觀、習俗和身份的廣泛討論<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Attenborough | first1 = Frederick T. | author-link1 = Frederick T. Attenborough | title = Discourse analysis and sexualisation: a study of scientists in the media |journal = Critical Discourse Studies | volume = 10| issue = 2| pages = 223–236 | publisher = [[Taylor_and_Francis|Taylor and Francis]] | doi = 10.1080/17405904.2012.736704 | date = 2013 | url = http://dx.doi.org/10.1080/17405904.2012.736704 | ref = harv| postscript = .}} [https://www.academia.edu/7595022/Discourse_analysis_and_sexualisation_a_study_of_scientists_in_the_media Online.]</ref>
；以及各種媒體裡出現許多與性相關的內容，例如色情文學、{{link-en|斜線小說|Slash fiction}}{{notetag|斜線小說是一種愛好者進行的二次創作小說，著重於角色間的同性戀愛或同性性關係。}}、性行為或自慰指南書、多種色情子類別；新型式的性經驗，例如以即時通訊、虛擬實境的方式從事性行為；社會大眾對制定及應對色情相關法規的討論出現分歧；媒體對性醜聞的報導、爭議與恐慌。<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Attwood | first = Feona | title = Sexed up: theorizing the sexualization of culture | journal = [[Sexualities_(journal)|Sexualities]] | volume = 9 | issue = 1 | pages = 77–94 | publisher = [[SAGE_Publications|Sage]] | doi = 10.1177/1363460706053336 | date = February 2006 | url = http://dx.doi.org/10.1177/1363460706053336 | ref = harv | postscript = . }} [http://shura.shu.ac.uk/50/1/fulltext.pdf Pdf.] {{Wayback|url=http://shura.shu.ac.uk/50/1/fulltext.pdf |date=20180720093839 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book | last = Attwood | first = Feona | title = Mainstreaming sex the sexualization of Western culture | publisher = I.B. Tauris | location = London | year = 2009 | isbn = 1845118278 }}</ref>

在英文中，「Pornographication」這個詞彙被用來描述性產業的風格和內容已經進入主流的文化（例如電視、流行音樂、主流電影）並成為主流文化的一部分，或是指某些主流媒體的文本和文化引用性產業的風格、形式或審美觀的情形變得更為突出。<ref>{{cite book | last1 = Paasonen | first1 = Susanna | last2 = Nikunen | first2 = Kaarina |last3 = Saarenmaa | first3 = Laura | authorlink1 = Susanna Paasonen | title = Pornification: sex and sexuality in media culture | publisher = Berg | location = Oxford New York | year = 2007 | isbn = 9781845207045 }}</ref>Brian McNair將這種現象描述為「主流文化色情化」（pornographication of the mainstream），<ref name=McNair>{{cite book | last = McNair | first = Brian | title = Striptease culture sex, media and the democratization of desire | publisher = Routledge | location = London New York | year = 2002 | isbn = 9780415237345 }}</ref>這種現象已經隨著色情文化和色情影片的領域擴展而逐漸發展，而色情或色情影片本身也得到了更多的受眾。根據Brian McNair所述，這兩項發展都可以在「[[脫衣舞|脫衣舞]]」這項文化的轉變中體現，這種文化破壞了後現代西方文化中公共和私人話題之間的界線。這種文化趨勢普遍地在生活方式、現實、互動性、自我暗示和公共親密。<ref name=McNair />

在所有年齡層中，和媒體接觸最多的年齡層是兒童和青少年，這是他們更容易接收到訊息、並受到該訊息影響的一段時間。孩童從媒體上接受性教育，他們暴露於性化的圖像與超量的訊息中，但卻不能、也沒有能力去處理它們，這將會影響他們的發展與行為。<ref name=Kilbourne />

年輕女孩在這個充斥性化媒體的環境中被塑造出的形象、讓大眾變得更容易接受將兒童視為「誘人與性感的」<ref name=Kilbourne />這使人們更難建立健康的性關係，並產生性別歧視的態度。性化還會助長性暴力與對兒童的性虐待。<ref name=Kilbourne />

== 批評 ==

澳大利亞的作家Catharine Lumby 和 Kath Albury在2010年出版的作品中批評，<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Lumby | first1 = Catharine | last2 = Albury | first2 = Kath | title = Introduction: children, young people, sexuality and the media | journal = Media International Australia | volume = 135 | issue = 1 | pages = 56–60 | publisher = [[SAGE_Publications|Sage]] | doi = 10.1177/1329878X1013500108 | date =2010-05 | url = http://dx.doi.org/10.1177/1329878X1013500108 | ref = harv | postscript = .}}</ref> 認為性化是「一場醞釀了近十年的論辯」，對性與媒體的關注早就不是新鮮事。而最近關於性化的文章多數是批評的，因為它採用「單方面、選擇性、過度簡化、歸納式的、否定態度」的引證方式。<ref name="Vanwesenbeeck2009">{{cite journal | last = Vanwesenbeeck | first = Ine | title = The risks and rights of sexualization: an appreciative commentary on Lerum and Dworkin's "''Bad Girls Rule''" | journal = [[Journal_of_Sex_Research|Journal of Sex Research]] | volume = 46 | issue = 4 | pages = 268–270 | publisher = [[Taylor_and_Francis|Taylor and Francis]] | doi = 10.1080/00224490903082694 | date = July 2009 | url = http://dx.doi.org/10.1080/00224490903082694 | ref = harv | postscript = .}}
* ''A commentary on'': {{cite journal | last1 = Lerum | first1 = Kari | last2 = Dworkin | first2 = Shari L. | title = "Bad Girls Rule": an interdisciplinary feminist commentary on the Report of the APA Task Force on the Sexualization of Girls | journal = [[Journal_of_Sex_Research|Journal of Sex Research]] | volume = 46 | issue = 4 | pages = 250–263 | publisher = [[Taylor_and_Francis|Taylor and Francis]] | doi = 10.1080/00224490903079542 | date = July 2009 | url = http://dx.doi.org/10.1080/00224490903079542 | ref = harv | postscript = .}}</ref>並且已經「在矚目與監管的言詞中達到飽和」。<ref name="Smith2010">{{cite journal | last = Smith | first = Clarissa | title = Pornographication: a discourse for all seasons | journal = International Journal of Media & Cultural Politics | volume = 6 | issue = 1 | pages = 103–108 | publisher = [[Publishing_Technology_plc|Ingentaconnect]] | doi = 10.1386/macp.6.1.103/3 | date = January 2010 | url = http://dx.doi.org/10.1386/macp.6.1.103/3 | ref = harv| postscript = .}}</ref>在這些著作與受到廣泛關注的報導中，批評者認為、這個詞通常被用做為「一個渴望兒童性交易的老頭同一個無緣無故引起一切的女孩眉來眼去」。<ref name="EganHawkes2008">{{cite journal | last1 = Egan | first1 = R. Danielle | last2 = Hawkes | first2 = Gail L. | title = Endangered girls and incendiary objects: unpacking the discourse on sexualization | journal = Sexuality & Culture, special issue: Sexuality, Sexualization and the Contemporary Child | volume = 12 | issue = 4 | pages = 291–311 | publisher = [[Springer_Science+Business_Media|Springer]] | doi = 10.1007/s12119-008-9036-8 | date = December 2008 | url = http://dx.doi.org/10.1007/s12119-008-9036-8 | ref = harv | postscript = .}}</ref>他們認為，這些論述往往忽視了媒體、性別與身體上的女性主義成果，並提出非常保守的性觀念，例如只有一夫一妻制中的異性性行為才是正常的。<ref name="LerumDworkin2009">{{cite journal | last1 = Lerum | first1 = Kari | last2 = Dworkin | first2 = Shari L. | title = "Bad Girls Rule": an interdisciplinary feminist commentary on the Report of the APA Task Force on the Sexualization of Girls | journal = [[Journal_of_Sex_Research|Journal of Sex Research]] | volume = 46 | issue = 4 | pages = 250–263 | publisher = [[Taylor_and_Francis|Taylor and Francis]] | doi = 10.1080/00224490903079542 | date = July 2009 | url = http://dx.doi.org/10.1080/00224490903079542 | ref = harv | postscript = .}}</ref>他們認為，這些論點傾向於忽略對性別表現與規範的任何歷史性理解，亦經常忽略性與媒體、文化與技術之間的理論與實務關係。<ref name=Scot /><ref name=EganHawkes2008 />

對女性的性化已經成為一個社會問題，而這應該要被避免，因位它會影響女性如何看待和表達自我。Patrice Oppliger在書籍《Girls Gone Skank》（當平凡女孩變成俗艷賤貨）的書評裡提出社會塑造個人興趣的方式。<ref>{{cite book | last = Oppliger | first = Patrice | author-link = Patrice Oppliger | title = Girls gone skank: the sexualization of girls in American culture | year = 2008 | publisher = McFarland and Company Inc. | location = Jefferson, North Carolina | isbn = 9780786435227 }}</ref> Amanda Mills談道：「因此、女孩被社會化，參與對自己的虐待，變成狂熱的消費者或改變自己的行為以反映性剝削的形象和商品。」<ref>{{cite journal | last = Mills | first = Amanda | title = Book review: "''Girls gone skank: the sexualization of girls in American culture''" by Patrice Oppliger | journal = [[Feminist_Review|Feminist Review]] | volume = 99 | issue = 1 | pages = e16–e17 | publisher = [[Palgrave_Macmillan|Palgrave Macmillan]] | doi = 10.1057/fr.2011.45 | date = November 2011 | url = http://dx.doi.org/10.1057/fr.2011.45 | ref = harv | postscript = .}}</ref> Audre Lorde 在自己的作品《色情的用途：以色情為力量》（Uses Of The Erotic: The Erotic As Power）中指出，對女性施加的抑制性色情女性導致她們感覺自己優於男人，「表面上，色情被積極地建立成男尊女卑的標記，但另一方面、女性也從中體會到苦處，並對此感到反感、蔑視並懷疑它的存在。<ref>{{cite book | last = Lorde | first = Audre | author-link = Audre Lorde | title = Uses of the erotic: the erotic as power | publisher = Kore Press | location = Tucson, Arizona | year = 2000 | origyear = 1984 | isbn = 9781888553109 }}
